{"parse":{"title":"Petru Maior","pageid":6705617,"revid":830867446,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Reghin13.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Reghin13.JPG/220px-Reghin13.JPG\" width=\"220\" height=\"330\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Reghin13.JPG/330px-Reghin13.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Reghin13.JPG/440px-Reghin13.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"547\" data-file-height=\"821\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Reghin13.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Petru Maior</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Petru Maior</b> (<small>Romanian pronunciation:&#160;</small><span title=\"Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)\" class=\"IPA\"><a href=\"/wiki/Help:IPA/Romanian\" title=\"Help:IPA/Romanian\">[\u02c8petru \u02c8major]</a></span>; 1761 in <a href=\"/wiki/T%C3%A2rgu_Mure%C8%99\" title=\"T\u00e2rgu Mure\u0219\">Marosv\u00e1s\u00e1rhely</a> <i>(now T\u00e2rgu Mure\u0219, Romania)</i> \u2013 14 February 1821 in <a href=\"/wiki/Budapest\" title=\"Budapest\">Budapest</a>) was a <a href=\"/wiki/Romanians\" title=\"Romanians\">Romanian</a> writer who is considered one of the most influential personalities of the <a href=\"/wiki/Age_of_Enlightenment\" title=\"Age of Enlightenment\">Age of Enlightenment</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Transylvania\" title=\"Transylvania\">Transylvania</a> (the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Transylvanian_School\" title=\"Transylvanian School\">Transylvanian School</a></i>). Maior was a member of the <a href=\"/wiki/Romanian_Church_United_with_Rome,_Greek-Catholic\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Romanian Church United with Rome, Greek-Catholic\">Greek-Catholic</a> clergy, a historian, philosopher, and linguist.\n</p><p>The <i>Buda Lexicon</i>, a book published in 1825, included two texts by Petru Maior, <i>Orthographia romana sive latino-valachica una cum clavi</i> and <i>Dialogu pentru inceputul linbei rom\u00e2ne</i>, in which he introduced the letters \u0219 for <span title=\"Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)\" class=\"IPA\">/\u0283/</span> and \u021b for <span title=\"Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)\" class=\"IPA\">/ts/</span>, which have since been in use in the <a href=\"/wiki/Romanian_alphabet\" title=\"Romanian alphabet\">Romanian alphabet</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Petru_Maior&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Marinella L\u00f6rinczi Angioni, \"Coscienza nazionale romanza e ortografia: il romeno tra alfabeto cirillico e alfabeto latino \", <i>La Ricerca Folklorica</i>, No. 5, La scrittura: funzioni e ideologie. (Apr., 1982), pp. 75\u201385.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Petru_Maior&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20151226205330/http://www.upm.ro/English/\">Petru Maior University: Our Patron</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.biserica.org/WhosWho/DTR/M/PetruMaior.html\">Dic\u0163ionarul Teologilor Rom\u00e2ni \u2013 Petru Maior</a> <span class=\"languageicon\">(in Romanian)</span></li></ul>\n<div role=\"navigation\" class=\"navbox\" aria-labelledby=\"Authority_control_frameless_&amp;#124;text-top_&amp;#124;10px_&amp;#124;alt=Edit_this_at_Wikidata_&amp;#124;link=https&amp;#58;//www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q897482&amp;#124;Edit_this_at_Wikidata\" style=\"padding:3px\"><table class=\"nowraplinks hlist navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit\"><tbody><tr><th id=\"Authority_control_frameless_&amp;#124;text-top_&amp;#124;10px_&amp;#124;alt=Edit_this_at_Wikidata_&amp;#124;link=https&amp;#58;//www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q897482&amp;#124;Edit_this_at_Wikidata\" scope=\"row\" class=\"navbox-group\" style=\"width:1%\"><a href=\"/wiki/Help:Authority_control\" title=\"Help:Authority control\">Authority control</a> <a href=\"https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q897482\" title=\"Edit this at Wikidata\"><img alt=\"Edit this at Wikidata\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Blue_pencil.svg/10px-Blue_pencil.svg.png\" width=\"10\" height=\"10\" style=\"vertical-align: text-top\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Blue_pencil.svg/15px-Blue_pencil.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Blue_pencil.svg/20px-Blue_pencil.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"600\" data-file-height=\"600\" /></a></th><td class=\"navbox-list navbox-odd\" style=\"text-align:left;border-left-width:2px;border-left-style:solid;width:100%;padding:0px\"><div style=\"padding:0em 0.25em\">\n<ul><li><span class=\"nowrap\"> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.worldcat.org/identities/containsVIAFID/100203148\">WorldCat Identities</a></span></li>\n<li><span class=\"nowrap\"><a href=\"/wiki/Integrated_Authority_File\" title=\"Integrated